<br>
A lvl 60 paladin and warrior in simliar gear....i would wager the warrior tanks about 5-7% better, and has 5-10% more hp, so mabye 15% better overall. These are just rough estimates. <br>
<br>
A level 60 paladin with maxed AA tank skills is a better tank then a nondefensive warrior with no AA skills. A warrior and paladin at 60 with maxed tank skills are about the same as without.<br>
<br>
This is ofcourse ignoring defensive, a defensive warrior is a much better tank for 3 minutes.<br>
<br>
That ofcourse ignores the other strenghts a paladin has that a warrior doesnt have. We can better keep agro which is a plus, but not always necessary. We can also mitigate some of the damage recieved through spells, we can heal some of that which a warrior cant.<br>
<br>
But, on the warriors side is also increased damage.<br>
<br>
Short and sweet tho, a lvl 51 is not a lvl 55. A 55 would do more damage and tank better, as well as hold agro better and the added spell benefit. Course the downside is a lvl 55 takes more exp from the group then a 51 would hehe. But, killing stuff faster and more efficiantly gets the group more exp faster. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useventhsword.showPublicProfile?language=EN>seventhsword</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/20/02 4:38:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15866.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ty</span><hr size=1> /confused.  <br>
